      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<h3 id=\"InstallationofRenderManforKatana-KatanaSupport\"><style>[data-colorid=hboz59yih9]{color:#3b73af} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=hboz59yih9]{color:#5088c4}[data-colorid=kcutx3qgot]{color:#3b73af} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=kcutx3qgot]{color:#5088c4}</style>Katana Support</h3><p>See <a href=\"/wiki/spaces/REN26/pages/19660947/Installation+and+Licensing\" data-linked-resource-id=\"19660947\" data-linked-resource-version=\"33\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Installation and Licensing</a> for the list of Katana versions that are supported.</p><h3 id=\"InstallationofRenderManforKatana-InstallationandLicensing\">Installation and Licensing</h3><p>RenderMan for Katana (RfK) can either be installed in one of two ways:</p><ol start=\"1\"><li><p>Use the&nbsp;RenderMan Installer&nbsp;which manages the downloading, installation, and licensing of RenderMan Pro Server (the actual renderer) along with RenderMan for Katana.&nbsp;</p></li><li><p>Download the RenderMan for Katana and RenderMan Pro Server packages from the forum Product Downloads page. The RPMs can be installed by hand.</p></li></ol><p>See the RenderMan<span data-colorid=\"hboz59yih9\"> </span><a href=\"/wiki/spaces/REN26/pages/19660947/Installation+and+Licensing\" data-linked-resource-id=\"19660947\" data-linked-resource-version=\"33\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\"><span style=\"color: rgb(59,115,175);\">Installation and Licensing</span></a><span data-colorid=\"kcutx3qgot\">&nbsp;</span>documentation for a more detailed explanation.</p><div class=\"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-information conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"1433e541-2857-40c9-8e3d-31ecea499cd4\" data-macro-name=\"info\"><span class=\"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-information-macro-icon\"> </span><div class=\"confluence-information-macro-body\"><p>If you have 3Delight installed, you'll need to set your DEFAULT_RENDERER environment variable to prman or change the renderer parameter in RenderSettings to prman.</p></div></div>"
    }
